  "number": 3497,
  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/3497",
  "title": "[RoutingManager]: getConfiguration uses a staled uiState",
  "body": "**Describe the bug 🐛**\r\n\r\nThe `RoutingManager.getConfiguration` uses a stale `uiState` to compute the parameters. It always uses the initial `uiState`. It leads to issue with dynamic add / remove of widgets. Each time one or the other occurs we call `getConfiguration` on every widgets to create the next search parameters. But the `uiState` might have changed since the instance start. It means that the search parameters are always computed like if it was a fresh start.\r\n\r\nThe issue does not occurs with every type of refinement. It only occurs on top level refinement like `query`, `hitsPerPage`, etc... It's because the implementation of `enhanceConfiguration` is not correct. With the correct behaviour the issue would happen on every refinements.\r\n\r\n**To Reproduce 🔍**\r\n\r\n1. Go to https://codesandbox.io/s/n15lol465j\r\n2. Type a query e.g. \"Apple\"\r\n3. Click outside of the `searchBox`\r\n3. Wait for the timeout (5000ms)\r\n4. The `rangeInput` widget is added\r\n\r\nNote that the `query` disappeared and the refinement is lost.\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior 💭**\r\n\r\nThe search parameters must stay the same after the add / remove widgets operation.\r\n\r\n**Additional context**\r\n\r\n> [Discourse post issue with Vue InstantSearch](https://discourse.algolia.com/t/preventing-multiple-api-hits-when-updating-geolocation-via-browser-api-query-parsing/7030)\r\n",
